  "prompt": "Is there any doubt that money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "No, there is no doubt that money laundering is illegal. Money laundering is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money to make it appear as though it came from legitimate sources. It is universally recognized as a crime under international law and the domestic laws of virtually every country.\n\nIn the United States, for example, money laundering is prohibited under the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) and the USA PATRIOT Act. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF), an international body, sets global standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing, and its recommendations have been adopted by over 200 countries and jurisdictions.\n\nMoney laundering is often associated with organized crime, drug trafficking, corruption, and terrorism financing. Penalties for money laundering can include hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and lengthy prison sentences. Therefore, it is widely and unequivocally understood that money laundering is illegal.",
